{
  "description": "A close-up photograph showcases a pristine, white Queen of the Night cactus bloom against a blurred, green background. The flower is in full bloom, displaying delicate, elongated petals that radiate outward from a central core. The petals transition from a pale yellow-green at the base to a creamy white towards the tips. Subtle hints of reddish-purple are visible at the petal tips, adding depth.  A second, unopened bud hangs below the blooming flower, exhibiting a darker reddish-purple hue. The composition emphasizes the ethereal beauty and fleeting nature of this nocturnal blossom. The background is a wash of out-of-focus greenery, suggesting a lush garden setting, with soft lighting that highlights the flower's form.",
